## 3. BRAIN DIVERGENCE MODEL (Live-Tested)

Location: `brain.py` → `get_brain_report()` L249-370

```
divergence_score starts at 0

Source 1: Politician cluster buys (≥3 buys → +2)
Source 2: Insider net buying (>$5M → +3, >$1M → +1)
Source 3: Insider net selling (≥3 sells → -2)
Source 4: Finnhub MSPR cross-reference [NEW]
  - Politician BUY + MSPR>50  → CONVERGENCE  (+3)
  - Politician BUY + MSPR<-20 → FADING INSIDERS (-2)
  - Politician SELL + MSPR>50 → DIVERGENCE    (-2)
  - Politician SELL + MSPR<-20→ BOTH EXITING  (+3)
Source 5: News catalysts (earnings, M&A → +1)
Source 6: Fed tone (HAWKISH/DOVISH alignment)
Source 7: Tavily enrichment (if Finnhub news misses → +1)
```

**Live test result:** Divergence boost = **5** (politician clusters + $16.1M insider net buying + dovish Fed)

### Convergence/Divergence Signals Detected (Live March 9)
```
NOW (buy):   DIVERGENCE ❌  boost=-2 → Politician fading insiders (MSPR=-100)
PYPL (sell): DIVERGENCE ❌  boost=-2 → Politician bailing while insiders buy (MSPR=100)
AAPL (buy):  CONVERGENCE ✅ boost=+1 → Both aligned (MSPR=26)
```

